    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add your <strong>pork mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>with your <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>garlic paste </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
